data.title: Halloween Fiesta
data.text: Excellent food (steak fajitas, fish tacos, camarones) and personable, attentive servers in a charming, festve environment! We had a wonderful meal and entertaining time interacting with the costumed staff 2 days before Halloween!

data.title: Great food but I'm sick of poor service
data.text: It started with their parking lot.  The spaces are so tight our Acadia fit white stripe to white stripe.  We got there at 5 pm for dinner so the lot was empty.  I like to wash up before I eat.  One bathroom stall the door doesn't close.  Both stalls had broken toilet seats.  My margarita ($5) was a helpful attitude adjustment.  The food was terrific. I had grilled fish tacos ($14) and my husband had the Flying Burrito ($13).  There was one other diner in the place.  I would have liked another margarita but never saw the server again.  When we were done, had to just get up and go to the hostess to pay.  This was our 47th anniversary dinner and I wish it had gone better.

data.title: Sit outside and enjoy a beverage as you dive in to the Best Chips!
data.text:
My friends go to Habaneros - a lot! They even named a sandwich after Bob...
Hands down, best Chips in Medford - great salsa...great service and I love the Grilled Fish Tacos. Superb - served with Black Beans, Rice, Chipotle Cream. Quite good!

data.title: Totally Awesome Food
data.text: We had seafood enchiladas that were amazing, and their chile rellenos were cooked perfectly.  If we lived in Medford we would be there once a week.  Also, very much enjoyed a strawberry margarita.

data.title: Pretty good & slightly spicy
data.text: Had chicken enchiladas verde. The pinto beans were yummy, as was the rice. However,  the black beans were undercooked & watery. Enchilada was alright. Pricing for lunch was moderate.

data.title: New owners, good food
data.text: A friend of mine and I have traveled around Southern Oregon looking for good nachos after work. Most locations have been disappointing.  We have discovered Habanero's is the exception.   Huge portion with shredded cheese, (not cheese sauce) highlights a delectable dish with all the fixings. An inexpensive happy hour also indicates we will be back. Family members also visited this place on a Friday night in late May and gave it rave reviews as well.

data.title: I can't believe we haven't tried this one before.
data.text:
I'm always looking for Chili Rellenos that I like.  I found them at Habanero's. On a Monday, when I didn't feel like cooking after having triple digits, my husband suggested dinner out.  A beautiful, clean restaurant with friendly help and excellent service.  Margaritas: very good & $5.00 on Monday.  He had the Carne Asada special with Guacamole & Enchilada, Beans & rice.  I had the excellent Chili Relleno with a Taco.
We split a Flan with whipped cream for dessert. It was good too.
We'll definitely return!

data.title: Best in Southern Oregon
data.text: Have been to this place a number of times, usually during the Medford Cruise in June.  Always had excellent food here--some of the best in Oregon!  I agree it can be very crowded at times, but we have always found it worth the wait.  Hope to visit again soon.

data.title: Large group dining............
data.text: Our club hosted a(belated) Holiday Dinner hear with a little over 30 people.  We had a buffet of Tacos, Fajitas, enchiladas and all the fixings, including beans and rice.  Good time was had by all and the food was good.  The waitress couldn't do enough for us, they were GREAT!!!!  The only downside was the party in the room next to us were SO Loud!!! we could here them.  They need some sort of a partition in between the rooms.

data.title: Great Service for a Large Group
data.text: There were 13 of us.  We were seated in a central location, not out of the way like so many other restaurants put large groups.  There was only one server assigned to our group, but she did really, REALLY well.  Drinks were ordered first and they came quickly.  Perhaps a little sparse on asking for fresh drinks when previous ones were empty, but I heard no complaints. Orders broken down by each couple, and everything arrived at the same time.  I had fajitas, and they came to the table RED hot and sizzling.  Heard no complaints from anyone in the group about anything.  Gratuity was automatically added (this is a sticking point with me, as I don't like to be forced into paying gratuity.  If the service is good, I'll tip.  If it's not so good, my tip might not be quite as generous.) Manager was gracious and even helped me take a group photo.

data.title: Poor Choice
data.text: Stopped by this place again. Same disappointing experience. To many people. The food was mediocre. The wait time was too long. Why bother. This place has a confused Identity. It does not Know if it wants to be a restaurant or a Nightclub. It does both fair, but neither great. Wanna play with drunks and crowds this is the place.

data.title: Good food and service, clean and friendly.
data.text: Good food, I like the pork chili Verde and order it every time I go to a new Mexican restaurant.  I was not disappointed.  I have returned several times, occasionally ordering the same dish and I have found them to be consistent.

data.title: Food poisoning
data.text:
FOOD POISONING!!!
I went to this restaurant with my family.  6 adults and 5 children.  My sister found a hair in her food,  I didn't eat anything along with several other members of my family because the food tasted disgusting,  and those that did eat ALL got sick that night.  Vomiting for hours! 
When asked for a refund on our very overpriced food the manager argued with us and eventually promised a refund which never happened.  
This place should be shut down until it learns about proper food handling.

data.title: Authentic atmosphere, good margaritas, great service, above average salsa!
data.text: I'm a gringo from the San Diego Mexican barrio and the blurred line of the Mexican border, so I am used to the best authentic Mexican food in the U.S. It is NOT to be found in Oregon. BUT Habaneros is very good for gringo Mexican. The ambience inside is right out of Mexico or better, very authentic, and the bartender-rita is worth the calories (they offer a cocktail menu)! You can choose whole black beans or frijoles, chips are always fresh and salsa good (but not spicy unfortunately!) Flavors are moderate overall. Fish tacos okay but fish is fresh. I always get the taco salad with extra cilantro. I have been many times, lunch and dinner, and service is always good and friendly. My husband likes the chile relleno, not soggy or greasy with a soft exterior and lots of cheese inside.

data.title: No flavor
data.text: Ok a Mexican restaurant needs to have flavor in their food. This place had no spice at all . The salsa tasted spoiled. The portions of food for the cost was of no value. I get better mexican food for taco bell and faster service. My water glass was empty before my food arrived and the waitress didn't refill it until we finished our meal even after asking for more several times for more. Cross this place off the list

data.title: Pleasing atmosphere.. Excellent Service
data.text:
We were a party of 16(6 were children) easily accommodated in a side party room. Comfortable and roomy! Our servers were attentive and gracious. I am a huge
Mexican food fan, that being said my meal was just average. I had the seafood enchilada, which I shared so the portion was good, but for me nothing special about the taste. I would definitely try on another trip to town and a different entre, as the service
was so great and I liked the atmosphere, we had a birthday girl and they sang well!

data.title: More American than Mexican
data.text: Service is friendly and attentive and the ambience is good -- I especially like the semi-industrial feel around the bar area. The food was okay, but that's the disappointment, I expected more. My fire roasted chicken was perfectly tender with the pleasant aroma of grilled chicken but sans any of the ethnic flavors I expect from Mexican cuisine. I needed some spice, some cilantro and some lemon/lime notes to come through.

data.title: Reunion of sorts
data.text: Small get together, 9 of us, seating was no problem, service was great, chips and salsa was good, seafood enchilada was very good.  Lots of fiod

data.title: Good service, nice atmosphere
data.text: Fresh chips and good spicy salsa. I ordered the steak fajitas and they came hot and sizzling as expected. Dinner is served with rice and a choice of black or pinto beans (I prefer black) which were very tasty. The fajitas were seasoned well and there was plenty - I could have split it with my husband had he been with me. My only disappointment was the chewy steak - could hardly bite through it and took more effort to chew than expected. The server was great and handled the busy dining room attentively with a big smile. I'll definitely go back to try something else on their menu.

data.title: Fish Tacos!!
data.text: Any time we are up in Medford running errands during the day, we always make it a point to stop at Habanero's for their fish tacos and a margarita.  Their fish tacos are absolutely the best and I've found myself at home making the chipotle dipping sauce when we cook Mexican.  My husband and I have eaten many, many fish tacos here in the USA as well as in Baja and Hawaii.  Habanero's by far makes the best fish tacos bar none.  To compliment this meal, a fruit margarita is perfect.  The service is great, the staff are wonderful and they have made a point of remembering us personally even though we only get up to Medford periodically.  We always feel at home eating at this restaurant and highly recommend it to those of you out there that are Mexican food lovers like us.  Enjoy!
